This past Saturday, a whopping 334 title deeds were handed out to beneficiaries of state-subsidised housing in Pennyville. Today, a further 15 new recipients received their title deeds. The Housing Department has further committed itself to ensuring that all completed housing units are allocated by the end of 2017/18 financial year. During the tabling of the 2017/18 Budget, it was announced that the City has allocated an operating budget of R152 million and a multi-year capital budget of R1.9 billion to fund the Johannesburg Social Housing Companyâ€™s (JOSHCO) purchase of buildings within the inner city. The City has over the past three months made 12 buildings available for the purpose of creating low cost quality housing within the inner city by working with the private sector.